## Pass 5: Quality Tests

### 5.1 Flow Test

| Criterion | ✓/✗ |
|-----------|-----|
| Hooks immediately? | |
| Logical progression? | |
| Transitions explicit? | |
| Conclusion earned? | |

### 5.2 One-Idea Test

| Slide # | Core Idea | Competing? | ✓/✗ |
|---------|-----------|------------|-----|
| | | | |

### 5.3 Evidence Test

| Slide # | Claims | In Summary? | ✓/✗ |
|---------|--------|-------------|-----|
| | | | |

### 5.4 Action Test

| Criterion | ✓/✗ |
|-----------|-----|
| Clear Action slide? | |
| WHO/WHAT/WHEN? | |
| Urgency clear? | |

### 5.5 Headline Test

List titles in sequence:
1. 
2. 
3. 
...

| Criterion | ✓/✗ |
|-----------|-----|
| Titles alone tell complete story? | |
| Stranger understands "so what"? | |
| Governing thought supported? | |
| Reviewable without slide content? | |

**If headlines don't tell the story, rewrite before proceeding.**

### 5.6 Red Thread Test

| # | Title | GT Connection | ✓/✗ |
|---|-------|---------------|-----|
| 1 | | | |
| 2 | | | |

**No clear connection → restructure, appendix, or cut.**

